text: Yanina Kuskova (born 11 December 2001) is an Uzbekistani road racing cyclist. She competed at the 2021 UCI Road World Championships, in the women's time trial event and women's road race event. She became national champion in 2020 and 2021 in both the road race and time trial events. She rides with Tashkent City Women Professional Cycling Team. == References == Category:2001 births Category:Cyclists Category:Living people
